cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE

The paper proposes a method for automatic detection of microaneurysms in retinal images using image processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves feature extraction and classification, which are related to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the proposed method uses a hybrid sampling/boosting classifier, which is a type of ensemble learning, indicating a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
